Consider a electric dipole formed by two charges $+q$ and $-q$, separated by a distance $d$, in an non uniform electric field $\bf{E}(\bf{r})$. Show, from the potential energy $E_P$, that the dipole is subject to a force $\bf{F}=(\bf{p}\cdot \nabla)\bf{E}$.\\ {\it Indication}: Use the relation
\begin{equation*}
\nabla\left(\frac{{\partial f}}{{\partial x_i}}\right)=\frac{{\partial}}{{\partial x_i}}\left(\nabla f\right)~.
\end{equation*}

