void echo() {
    char buf[100];
    scanf("%s", buf);
    printf(buf);
}
\end{lstlisting}

A vehicle is in linear motion. The scalar velocity as a function of time is given by

\begin{equation*}
v(t) = b_0t^2 -\,a_0t\ ,
\end{equation*}

where $b_0$ and $a_0$ are positive constants. Determine the average velocity $\bar{v}(t)$ at time $t$.

A homogeneous rod of length $L$ and mass $M$ rotates in a vertical plane around the horizontal axis $\boldsymbol{OG}$ at constant angular velocity $\boldsymbol{\dot{\psi}} = \dot{\psi}\,\boldsymbol{e}_3$. The axis $\boldsymbol{OG}$ rotates around the vertical axis $\boldsymbol{\hat{z}}$ at constant angular velocity $\boldsymbol{\dot{\phi}} = \dot{\phi}\,\boldsymbol{e}_z$. The moment of inertia of the rod with respect to its axis is $I_{G\parallel}$ and the torques perpendicular to the axis of the rod passing through $G$ are $I_{G\perp}$. The distance $|\boldsymbol{OG}| = R$.

a) Show that the angular momentum $\boldsymbol{L}_G$ is expressed in the principal axis frame $(G,\boldsymbol{e}_1,\boldsymbol{e}_2,\boldsymbol{e}_3)$ attached to the rod,

\begin{equation*}
\boldsymbol{L}_G = -\,I_{G\parallel}\,\dot{\phi}\,\sin\psi\,\boldsymbol{e}_1 -\,I_{G\perp}\,\dot{\phi}\,\cos\psi\,\boldsymbol{e}_2 + I_{G\perp}\,\dot{\psi}\,\boldsymbol{e}_3\ .
\end{equation*}

A mass $m$ is suspended on a spring of natural length $l_0$ and of elastic constant $k$. The spring is attached to a piston. The vertical motion of the piston is described by the equation

\begin{equation*}
s\left(t\right) = s_0\cos\left(\omega t\right)\ .
\end{equation*}

Show that the equation of motion can be recast as,

\begin{equation*}
\ddot{x}\left(t\right) + c_1\,x\left(t\right) = c_1\,s\left(t\right)\ ,
\end{equation*}

where $x\left(t\right) = z\left(t\right) + c_2$ with $z\left(t\right)$ the vertical position coordinate oriented downwards and $c_1$ and $c_2$ constants to be determined.

